latestIgtvVideos.title: College Adda with Sapan Verma - Trailer | Zomato Originals
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
College life, canteen food and lots of nostalgia!
Sapan Verma and his friends go back to their iconic colleges to eat some of the best canteen food and chill with the students.

Season 1 features Kusha Kapila at NIFT Delhi, Vipul Goyal at IIT Mumbai, Prashasti Singh at IIM Lucknow and Faye D'souza at Mount Carmel Bangalore.

Here's how to watch the show for FREE:
Open the Zomato app --> Click on the Videos tab at the bottom right --> Look for College Adda --> Watch and enjoy all four episodes

Which college should we visit next and which guest? Do comment and let us know

latestPosts.caption:
NEW SHOW! NEW TITLE! NEW POSTER!
So excited to be touring (very slowly) with the new hour that l’ve built in the last six months or so.
Ticket link in my bio
(Will keep adding more cities, tell where to come?)

ABOUT THE SHOW:
Sapan turned 35, became a father and also got high in Amsterdam - all within a year, but not particularly in that order.

He is cruising through life with mental burnout, a needless sense of superiority over Gen-Z and of course, chronic lower back pain.

Come, watch him have a meltdown on stage, and feel better about your own life.

Audiences have called this show “hilarious”, “so fresh and likeable” and “where are we going for dinner now” according to Sapan who has been hearing these people from behind the curtains as they leave after the show.

Get your tickets for a hilarious new hour of standup comedy before they sell out as he becomes insanely famous and inaccessible - a mild threat he’s been using since 2011.

See youuu ♥️

latestPosts.caption:
Okay WOW — this was hands down one of the most fun (and totally unhinged 👀) things I’ve ever done! Had the best time shooting Plum Skin City with @mojorojo and @sapanv — the chaos, the chemistry, the comedy... simply unmatched. 😂 

S1E3 is live and it’s a wild ride with a twist. A gift hamper is up for grabs, and things get competitive real quick. Who wins? The one who actually knows what hyaluronic acid is or the one who just learned to pronounce it? Watch the whole episode now on @plumgoodness’ YouTube — link in their bio, because let’s be honest, I know we’re all lazy to search. 😉
